rComments: His lectures are actually entertaining, he's the sweetest guy and he's pretty funny too! The course is an easy A if you're good at writing, but if not its gonna be difficult. No quizzes, tests or hw just papers and the final exam (hes pretty helpful for the final exam though). A very entertaining class and the nicest prof I've had
Best professor. Hes funny, caring, and givers fantastic lectures. He posts everything online and then textbook isnt mandatory nor are the readings. Amazing course and amazing prof

Out of my 4 years of university, Prof. Danjoux has been the most intelligent, sincere. passionate and entertaining lecturer I have had. I wish I had his class first year, he would have inspired me to pursue teachers college. Truly incredible teaching style and content. Amazing course.

Dr. Danjoux is such a caring and passionate prof, anyone would be lucky to have him! However, his slides aren't detailed, so it'd be best to take thorough notes in lecture. I'm sure this was just an issue for my class specifically, but myself and many others have noticed that our TA's marking is pretty unfair and inconsistent with every assignment.
Nice teacher and obviously cares about his students and his subject. His teaching style is unique though and I found it did not work for me. Classes were often long and boring.

Ilan Danjoux is a gem. He sincerely cares about students' well being and wants them to learn and grow! Classes are super interactive, fun, and engaging and never like a lecture. He tells lots of funny stories, uses videos, and plays games to explain class concepts. Always super sweet and accommodating. Good human being and very inspiring.
